post_text:
YPS Parents and York Community Members -

I participated in the Four Corners risk dial zoom this morning and learned the dial will be set at 2.0 for the Four Corners area. That means their dial is on the line between yellow and orange. The reason the dial increased from last week is primarily due to Butler and Seward counties. The positivity rate and the number of cases increased in those counties.

The York county positivity rate decreased and the number of cases in the past week decreased as well.

Based on this information and collaborating with Four Corners Public Health, YPS will continue to stay in the yellow. We will continue to do everything we are doing now to mitigate risk.

I truly believe that our plan is working and we must not let our "guard" down.

Have a great Labor Day weekend.

Mitch Bartholomew - Superintendent

post_text:
Here is an update from the Post Prom Committee..........

2020 Daddy Daughter Dance

Thank you for your patience in the rescheduling of last year’s Daddy Daughter Dance. We have a new date and place. Obviously with the Covid-19 situation we are taking precautions to help keep everyone safe. We will be splitting the girls into groups according to their 2019-2020 school age. Those who have more than one daughter will be asked to come at their designated time. If you want to come at only one time slot, then please contact Kelly @ 402-631-8209 to make arrangements.

New Date: Saturday, October 3rd
New Location: Cornerstone Ag & Event Center: 2400 N Nebraska Ave
Times:
PreK/Kinder/1st: 3-4:30 with check-in @2:45
2nd/3rd: 5-6:30 with check-in @4:45
4th/5th: 7-8:30 with check-in @6:45
**Remember this is based on last school year’s grade level**

Girls will be required to wear a mask and masks are recommended for chaperones also.
Thank you!
Post Prom Committee

post_text:
Homecoming Week 2020

Homecoming Week will take place during the week of Sep. 8-11. During the week, YHS students will participate in dress-up days and hallway decorating. We will choose Homecoming King and Queen candidates, and vote on the King and Queen. Coronation will take place at halftime of the football game on September 11.

Based on our current situation, we have had to cancel some of the traditional homecoming festivities, due to the high risk-level involved. We unfortunately have to cancel the Spirit March, the Bonfire/Pep Rally, and the Homecoming Dance.

In order to prevent a large group gathering, there will be no in-person Fall Sports Parents Meeting in the theater on August 9th at 7:00pm. Instead, all information will be released via a Loom video. The link to this video will be posted on the school website.

Volleyball will also be releasing a Loom video for all parents. Coach Ericson will be sending more information your way on how to access that information.

All other fall sports, (Boys Tennis, Girls Golf, Boys and Girls Cross Country, Softball, and Football) will still hold in-person meetings at 7:15pm on August 9th. Each team will have its own location and separate entrances as follows:

Football- Aux Gym (Enter through the East doors of the Aux Gym)

Softball- Main Gym (Enter through the Main Activities Entrance)

Cross Country- Media Center (Enter through the Main YHS Entrance)

Girls Golf- Mr. Miller's Classroom (Enter through Coach Miller's back classroom door)

Boys Tennis- Cafeteria (Enter through the East door leading to the cafeteria)

Advance Services Inc.- York
July 29 at 1:00 PM ·

Advance Services is hiring bus drivers for 2020-2021 school year. Will be responsible for transporting students to and from school daily, field trips and school activities. We are also looking for someone to drive the school Suburban on various routes throughout the day. Would prefer someone with larger vehicle experience as buses vary in size depending on the route or activity but not required. Position requires a High School diploma or GED, a good driving record, unrestricted motor vehicle operator’s license with a school bus permit or willing to obtain correct endorsements for the position. Please contact Advance Services at 402-362-7638 or apply online at www.advanceservices.com
EOE

post_text:
Are you a college student who just found out your coursework is going online or have decided to take online courses instead of going back to school? Or are you a York College student looking for a part time job in education? We have an idea for a part-time or full-time job! Consider applying to be a paraprofessional at YPS.

Advance Services is hiring for Para Professionals for the 2020-2021 school year. Multiple positions and both part-time and full-time options are available working with grades K-12 students with developmental, social, emotional needs and learning disabilities. Hours will follow the student hours and school schedule.
Please apply online at www.advanceservices.com or call 402-362-7638 for more information.
EOE

shared_text:
Rochelle Geiger
June 23 at 6:21 PM ·

If your child was on free or reduced lunch in Nebraska this last school year, you may be eligible for Pandemic EBT (similar to Food Stamps/SNAP). Up to $281 per child. This program is not based on income, only on your child's free or reduced lunch status. Call the SNAP outreach hotline at 1-855-444-5556 to apply. It only takes 5 minutes to apply. Please have your child's student ID ready.
(This is a state issued ID and you’d need to ask your school principal/secretary for this number.)

If you already receive SNAP benefits, you will automatically receive this benefit. If you do not currently receive SNAP but your child was enrolled in free/reduced lunch please give them a call to apply!

Duke of the Year - Ross Fraser

Male Musician of the Year - Sam Heitz

He plays for sectionals and class as well as agreed to accompany students for District Music Contest.

Female Musician of the Year - Sophia Chavanu
Sophia Chavana is a strong musical leader in the classroom. She is a vocal leader in her section. She too contributes her musical abilities by playing the piano for sectionals and District Music Contest.

FULL-TIME CUSTODIAN

York Public Schools is looking to hire a full-time custodian to begin work on/about July 13th. This position is 40+ hours a week for 12-months a year. The beginning hourly wage will be $12.75. Paid holidays and health insurance are part of our competitive fringe benefits package.

Interested applicants need to send in a cover letter, the application that can be found at www.yorkpublic.org (https://wp.me/P9Ay8O-1j), and letters of recommendation by the deadline of June 15th. Interviews will take place the week of June 22nd.

Mail application materials to:
CUSTODIAN VACANCY
York Public Schools
1715 N. Delaware Avenue
York, NE 68467

post_text:
YPS Students, Families, and York Community -

I hope this message finds you safe and healthy. YPS teachers and staff continue to work hard for our students and families and I'm very proud of the effort I'm seeing.

We have made a slight adjustment to our last student day for the 2019-20 school year. Typically the last two or three days in each building include taking finals, field trips, and end of the year celebrations. Since we are not able to bring students back, we have decided to make Friday, May 15th our last student day. This will shorten our calendar by 2.5 days.

The YPS administrative team has several decisions to make in the next couple of weeks. Please be checking our COVID-19 landing page at www.yorkpublic.org for any updates.

Mitch Bartholomew - Superintendent

REMINDER - Due to the school closure caused by COVID-19, York Public Schools is offering free sack meals for breakfast and lunch for children ages 1 to 18 that live in the York School District!

We have 4 convenient locations - the east side of York Middle School, Harrison Park, York County Fairgrounds, and Orscheln's parking lot from 11:30 am to 1:30 pm, Monday-Friday, until June 30, 2020. Meals will be distributed in a drive-thru manner. Please pull up in line and meals will be brought to your vehicle.

YPS will provide 1 sack lunch for the current day and 1 sack breakfast for the next day per student. On Fridays, YPS will distribute meals for Friday lunch, Saturday and Sunday breakfast and lunch, and Monday breakfast.

No adult meals will be distributed.

Tonight at 820 pm (2020 military time), York Public Schools will join the national, "Be the Light," campaign, and turn on our stadium lights at East Hill Stadium. The lights will remain on for 20 minutes honoring the class of 2020.
Please feel free to drive by, observe, and honk your horn for the class of 2020. This will be in conjunction with the York Cruise Night tonight.

https://www.yorknewstimes.com/family/join-in-on-york-cruise-night-tonight/article_f99ba62c-7ae0-11ea-8a65-bb62cce69563.html

Please do not stop or get out of your vehicle in order to follow the Governor's guidelines for social distancing and grouping.
Even if you cannot make it to the stadium, turn on your house lights at 820 pm for the Class of 2020. We miss and care about you very much.
#ForeverADuke

York Public Schools Opening for the 2020-21 School Year

Speech-Language Pathologist or K-5 Special Education Teacher

York Public Schools, a progressive Class B district just 45 minutes west of Lincoln, is looking for an outstanding speech-language pathologist or a K-5 special education teacher.

Interested candidates are encouraged to submit a resume, cover letter, and credentials to Dr. Mitch Bartholomew, Superintendent of Schools, 1715 North Delaware Ave. York, NE 68467. We plan to review applicant files and schedule interviews as soon as possible.

Visit www.yorkpublic.org or e-mail mitch.bartholomew@yorkdukes.org for more info. EOE.

post_text:
This is information from The Food Bank of Lincoln. We are just sharing the information for them to help those in need.

The Food Bank of Lincoln will be in York to host our monthly distribution at East Hill Church of Christ this Friday, April 3rd, from 12:00 - 1:00. As you might expect, our distribution will look different this month. We will offer a drive-thru service. Guests will park (in a line), a food bag(s) will be placed beside their vehicle, and they will need to step out and place the bag(s) into their vehicle. We plan (cleared with YPD) to have vehicles line up on Florida Avenue, from the north, and turn right into the south parking lot of the church. We will not allow vehicles to turn left into that lot. Hopefully, this will keep traffic flowing smoothly.

March 15, 2020

YPS Families - We received updated and new information from Four Corners Health. If you are returning from Level 3 Countries (European Countries, China, South Korea, Japan, Iran) or from California, Washington State, or New York City, they are implementing Self-Quarantine and Monitoring for 14 days. This is a new protocol that is implemented in Nebraska.

If you have recently traveled from any of these locations, your student will be excused from school for the duration of the quarantine period. Please communicate with the school that your student attends so we're aware of who is under the self-quarantine protocol. Also, please contact Four Corners Health Department if you have recently traveled from these locations at – 402-362-2621.

Mitch Bartholomew, Superintendent

As you may or may not know, Chris “The Legend” Holder is retiring at the end of this school year. We would love for people to share a memory, a funny anecdote, a sincere (or backhanded) compliment, a canonization, a memorializing sonnet, or any other form of tribute you see fit. These mementos will be collected and arranged into a booklet to give to Chris upon her retirement. We know this will be a keepsake she will treasure for years to come.

You may email your responses to Angie Kroger (angie.kroger@yorkdukes.org) or Susan Kringle (susan.kringle@yorkdukes.org). If you’d prefer to send a hand-written tribute, you may send them to:

Attn: Angie Kroger
York High School
1005 Duke Drive
York, NE 68467

This is meant to be a surprise for Chris, so please don’t spill the beans - don't worry, she doesn't have Facebook. Thank you for your attention to this very important request. If you know someone who would like to contribute to this please share this with them.

post_text: We are incredibly PROUD of the York Dukes who will be competing in the STATE Academic Decathlon in Omaha on Friday and Saturday this week. To our knowledge, this is the first team from YHS to ever qualify for state Academic Decathlon. It is a rigorous state tournament format, and on Friday the students will give a 4 minute prepared speech to judges, a 2 minute extemporaneous type speech to judges, and have a 7 minute interview with judges. Essays were submitted by the decathletes in early February and they will compete in tests in math, literacy, science, music, art, and economics. The lone event that is available for the public to watch is the SUPER QUIZ on Saturday at 2:15 PM in the area of social studies. There are three levels of competitors: C students, B students, and A students. Two of the A students, Alyssa Gilliland and Anthonie Gomez had a rare PERFECT score during the super quiz at regionals earlier this semester. AWESOME! We hope that they continue to roll tomorrow and Take State! (photo and design credits to York News Times)

shared_text:

January 24 at 6:17 PM ·

Here is the other version of the positive-thinking tools we presented at #YorkMLK2020. Please let us know how this works for your kids (and for YOU)!
text:
Sam and Jill Ferguson presented this session at our #YorkMLK20 conference on Monday about a positive mindset, gratitude, and mindfulness. We are thrilled to announce that they will be our opening keynotes at the #YorkMLK21 conference on January 18, 2021. You might even see The Big Red Piano. 🎶 🎹 🎈 Teachers who have attended this conference the past few years have learned a variety of things that can be implemented in classrooms.

NDE Early Childhood
January 15 at 9:58 PM ·

Congratulations Kris Friesen at York Public Schools for successful completion of Nebraska's NAESP PreK3 Leadership Academy.

Through the academy, Kris worked towards implementing home visits in kindergarten, gathering data on Pre-K students attending kindergarten to help them be successful, and working with stakeholders to braid funding within the community for quality early childhood programming.

Thanks for supporting early childhood education and the development of leaders! #NAESPPreK #ilovepublicschools
